<subSubSection pageNumber="708" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="708">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="708">Note:</emphasis>
As pointed out by Harley (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="708">Watsonia</emphasis>
14: 86. 1982), Ietswaart (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="708">Leiden Bot. Ser.</emphasis>
4: 88. 1980) designated 743.12 (LINN) as the type of both 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Origanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="syriacum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="708">O. syriacum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="L. In" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1763" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Origanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="maru">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="708">O. maru</emphasis>
L. In
</taxonomicName>
clarifying this situation, Harley stated that the sheet in question &quot;is unquestionably the type of 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="708">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1763" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Origanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="maru">O. maru</taxonomicName>
&quot;
</emphasis>
, thereby typifying the name himself.
</paragraph>
